HEADWORD: Noetian
<hw>No*e"tian</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld>
<def>One of the followers of <persfn><etsep>Noetus</etsep></persfn>, who
lived in the third century. He denied the distinct personality of the
Father, Son, and Holy Ghost.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

